<div id="PJA13d182" class="doc letter">

<h2>From Antoine Marie Cerisier</h2>

<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Excellence</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Amsterdam 18 Aout 1782</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Jai vu ici Mr le Comte de Sharsfield qui ma fait lhonneur de me rendre visite; il ma parl du manuscrit quil vous avait communiqu et ma paru mme desirer que jen eusse aussi communication;<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n1" id="PJA13d183n1-ptr">1</a> il ma renvoy au tens o il aurait termin son voyage quil ne fait disait-il, que pour mettre la dernire main  cet ouvrage; je ne doute cependant que, sil tait  la Haye, il fit la moindre difficult de me le procurer pour deux ou trois jours; il y a certaines choses que je voudrais bien examiner; si vous naviez aucune objection  me lenvoyer par Mr Guild. Je vais me jetter bientt sur le grand sujet de la pacification gnrale; jai vu vos reflexions dans le Courier du Bas-Rhin et dans la gazette de Leide; je pourrai en ajouter des miennes;<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n2" id="PJA13d183n2-ptr">2</a> je desirerai beaucoup davoir le trait de commerce, tel quil se trouve actuellement arrang. Je vous prie detre persuad de lentier dvoument &amp; de la profonde venration avec les quelles jai lhonneur dtre votre trs humble &amp; trs obeissant servit</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">A M. Cerisier</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>Si vous aviez a mcrire confidentiellement, je vous prierai de mettre cette adresse  <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mr Lain Horloger vis  vis de la Tour de la mon noye<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n3" id="PJA13d183n3-ptr">3</a> pour remettre  Mr Robert</span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="PJA13d183" class="trans letter">

<h2>Antoine Marie Cerisier to John Adams: A Translation</h2>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Excellency</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Amsterdam, 18 August 1782</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I had the honor of a visit from Mr. Sarsfield here. He spoke to me about a manuscript that he sent to you, and he seemed to want me to see a copy of it also.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n1" id="PJA13d183n1-ptr">1</a> He deferred giving me a copy until after his trip, which, he said, he was only making to put final touches on this work. I doubt that he had the least bit of difficulty in getting it for me for a few days while he was at The Hague. There are some things in it that I would like to look at closely. If you have no objections, send it to me by way of Mr. Guild. I will soon be plunging into the great subject of general pacification. I saw your thoughts in the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Courier du Bas-Rhin</span> and the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette de Leyde</span>, to which I could add my own.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n2" id="PJA13d183n2-ptr">2</a> I would really like to have a copy of the commercial treaty as it stands now. I ask you to be persuaded of my entire devotion and deep veneration, with which I have the honor to be, your very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">A M. Cerisier</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>If you need to write to me confidentially, please use this address, at <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mr. Lain, watchmaker, opposite the mint tower,<a class="ptr" href="#PJA13d183n3" id="PJA13d183n3-ptr">3</a> to be delivered to Mr. Robert</span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="PJA13d183sn1">

   <p>
<span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</span>
</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="ADMS-06-13-02-pb-0252">[252]</span>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d183n1-ptr" id="PJA13d183n1">1</a>

   <p>For Guy Claude, Comte de Sarsfield, see vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0125" class="document">9:228229</a>. The manuscript that he sent to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> cannot be identified from Cerisiers description. Sarsfield wrote to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> on 10 Sept. (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>), indicating that he had sent <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> a manuscript that morning that touched on events in the Swiss canton of Bern, but that cannot be otherwise identified. At breakfast on 8 Oct., Sarsfield gave <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> his essay on slavery dated 27 Sept. and entitled Quelques Considrations sur LEsclavage, La Servitude De La Glebe, LEtat de Libert qui leur a succed Et les Effects qui Resultent des uns Et des autres. That essay is included in a 280-page collection of Sarsfields writings in the <span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span> that included pieces on the constitution of the Netherlands; the provincial constitutions of Utrecht, Gelderland, Friesland, Zeeland, Groningen, Drenthe, and Overijssel; the banks of Holland; the dikes of the Netherlands; the development of civilization; economics; and women (filmed at [<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">ca. 17821783</ins>], <span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers, Microfilms</span>, Reel No. 359).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d183n2-ptr" id="PJA13d183n2">2</a>

   <p>This is <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s A Memorial to the Sovereigns of Europe, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0099" class="document">[<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">ca. 58 July</ins>]</a>, above, that appeared in the two papers on 10 and 13 Aug., respectively. It appeared in Cerisiers <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Le politique hollandais</span> of 26 August.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d183n3-ptr" id="PJA13d183n3">3</a>

   <p>Located in Sophia Pleine or Square in the middle of Amsterdam.</p>

</div>
</div>
